summary: Diff adds frontend edit/delete UI controls across Equipment, Spare Parts, Maintenance, Cataloguing, and Documents pages, introduces a reusable ConfirmDialog, and extends React Query hooks with update/delete mutations and invalidations. Backend main.mo is modified but the provided snippet is truncated before any new update/delete methods can be confirmed.

hallucinated_features.description: Added URL parameter/sessionStorage utilities for persisting and clearing URL parameters (including hash-routing support), which are not part of the requested edit/delete asset management functionality.
hallucinated_features.reason: BuildRequest does not mention adding URL parameter parsing/persistence utilities; it focuses on CRUD mutations and UI controls for asset records.

hallucinated_features.description: Actor initialization flow now reads a secret admin token from URL parameters and calls a backend access-control initialization method, plus it invalidates/refetches nearly all React Query queries when the actor changes.
hallucinated_features.reason: BuildRequest constraints/non-goals do not request admin-token URL handling or broad query invalidation/refetch behavior tied to actor recreation; the request is specifically about adding edit/delete operations and targeted invalidation for affected lists.
